.TH PLSTRIPA 3plplot  "May, 2005" "" "PLplot API"
.SH NAME
\fBplstripa\fP - Add a point to a stripchart 
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBplstripa\fP(\fIid\fP, \fIp\fP, \fIx\fP, \fIy\fP)
.SH DESCRIPTION

.P
Add a point to a given pen of a given stripchart. There is no need for all pens to have the same number of points or to be equally sampled in the x coordinate. Allocates memory and rescales as necessary. 
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIid\fP (PLINT, input) 
Identification number (set up in \fBplstripc\fP(3plplot)) of the stripchart. 
.TP
\fIp\fP (PLINT, input) 
Pen number (ranges from 0 to 3). 
.TP
\fIx\fP (PLFLT, input) 
X coordinate of point to plot. 
.TP
\fIy\fP (PLFLT, input) 
Y coordinate of point to plot. 

